SIMPLE: scrupulous
RECORDS: 1

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Scrupulous
<hw>Scru"pu*lous</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>a.</pos> <ety>[L.
<ets>scrupulosus</ets>: cf. F. <ets>scrupuleux</ets>.]</ety> <sn>1.</sn>
<def>Full of scruples; inclined to scruple; nicely doubtful; hesitating
to determine or to act, from a fear of offending or of doing
wrong.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>Abusing their liberty, to the offense of their weak brethren which
were <qex>scrupulous</qex>.</q> <rj><qau>Hooker.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>Careful; cautious; exact; nice; <as>as,
<ex>scrupulous</ex> abstinence from labor; <ex>scrupulous</ex>
performance of duties</as>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>3.</sn> <def>Given to making objections; captious.</def>
<mark>[Obs.]</mark>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>Equality of two domestic powers⟦br⟧
Breed <qex>scrupulous</qex> faction.</q> <rj><qau>Shak.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>4.</sn> <def>Liable to be doubted; doubtful; nice.</def>
<mark>[Obs.]</mark>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>The justice of that cause ought to be evident; not obscure, not
<qex>scrupulous</qex>.</q> <rj><qau>Bacon.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><syn><b>Syn.</b> -- Cautious; careful; conscientious;
hesitating.</syn>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p> -- <wordforms><wf>Scru"pu*lous*ly</wf>, <pos>adv.</pos> --
<wf>Scru"pu*lous*ness</wf>, <pos>n.</pos></wordforms>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Scrutable</ent>⟦br⟧
